The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Life term for tourist rape trio
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Life term for tourist rape trio
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Gaya, May 17: In a speedy trial, three persons accused of gangraping a Japanese tourist on April 16 were sentenced to rigorous life imprisonment today.        
	Though the case was registered against five persons, only three were arrested, chargesheeted and subsequently put on fast trial in the court of the district and sessions judge.         
	The two others, including the main accused Lotan, are absconding. Two of the three convicts, according to the police, happened to be at the place of occurrence by chance and joined the group of rapists.        
	Gaya district and sessions judge J.K. Sen found the three accused  Lootan, alias Anuj, Pappu Kumar and Udai  guilty of gangrape under Section 376(G) of the IPC carrying the punishment of life imprisonment. They were also convicted under Sections 379 (theft) and 411 (possession of stolen property) and awarded three years imprisonment each under Sections 379 and 411. The sentences will run concurrently, said the judgment. Each of them was also fined of Rs 10,000.        
	The Japanese tourist was raped in Amwan village near Bodh Gaya on April 16 when she was on way to Gaya in an autorickshaw to catch a train.                                                                                                                                                           
